sql:
SELECT AVG(reaction_time) AS average_reaction_time
FROM responses
WHERE condition = (SELECT condition_id FROM conditions WHERE condition_name = 'Control');

external_knowledge:
- "Reaction time" refers to the time taken by participants to respond to tasks; 
- "Conditions" under which tasks were performed may include factors like environment or instructions; 
- Participants' characteristics (age, gender, ethnicity, education level, occupation, native language) are crucial for understanding their behavior and performance; 
- The task types are categorized (e.g., categorization, recognition, etc.), each potentially requiring different cognitive skills.
